headline: My Top 10 Stocks to Buy in 2024 Are Beating the Market by 48%. Should You Buy Them for 2025?
summary: If you'd instead put your $10,000 into an S&P 500 (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC) index fund, you would've had just $11,900 at the end of the year.  With $10,000 invested equally across those 10 stocks at the beginning of the year, you'd have $14,281 as of the Dec. 5 market close.  An equal investment in an S&P 500 index fund would be worth $12,890.

headline: Lululemon price target raised to $440 from $380 at Baird
summary: Baird raised the firm’s price target on Lululemon (LULU) to $440 from $380 and keeps an Outperform rating on the shares. The firm said its results included better-than-feared performance in the US and on gross margin while offering reassuring commentary regarding early holiday trends and a confident tone in merchandising course corrections for Spring 2025. headline: Lululemon price target raised to $360 from $325 at Bernstein
summary: Bernstein analyst Aneesha Sherman raised the firm’s price target on Lululemon (LULU) to $360 from $325 and keeps a Market Perform rating on the shares. Lululemon’s Q3 print was a small beat with a big stock reaction, the combination of a squeeze and growing optimism on FY25 and beyond, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
